1. Executive Summary of Findings

We have extended the ST-T1024 architecture with a formal proof-of-safety logic addressing the critical gaps previously identified in IEC 61508 assessments. Our analysis concludes:

1. Correctness is architecturally guaranteed via auditable, trusted ROM sourcing.
2. Routing determinism is closed via the FIS (Fuzzy Inference System), which is verifiable as a finite rule set.
