2. The Correctness Proof: Trusted ROM + Verifiable FIS

The original white paper established determinism (no hallucinations). This paper establishes correctness (right answer, every time).

2.1. Knowledge Immutability (75% ROM)

· Sourcing: The immutable core is derived exclusively from well-known, publicly audited basics knowledge sites (e.g., NIST, ISO, WHO, established encyclopedias).
· Implication: The ROM contains no opaque, unverifiable "learned" artifacts. It contains mathematical constants, physical laws, and safety boundaries that are internationally recognized and stable.
· IEC 61508 Translation: Systematic Capability (SC) is achieved. The safety logic is traceable to an external standard document. This resolves the "black box" objection.

2.2. Routing Integrity (FIS)

· Mechanism: The FIS is not a stochastic neural net. It is a deterministic set of fuzzy rules and finite-state logic.
· Proof: The FIS explicitly handles domain triage (e.g., Math vs. Medicine). Because it is rule-based, it is formally verifiable using model-checking tools (e.g., TLA+).
· IEC 61508 Translation: This closes the "misrouting" hazard. A query cannot be sent to the wrong tile, preventing contextual hallucination.

2.3. Ternary Logic Engine

· Precision: 1.58-bit logic (-1, 0, +1) eliminates floating-point arithmetic uncertainty.
· Reproducibility: Simulation = Benchmarking. Every execution trace is deterministic across all hardware instances.

